			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I never really understood how chanters feel when some broke a mez on an add until I started using my bards mez songs so much in BoT.  It never fails my last group with have a shammy you is into using his DoTs like crazy.  We zone into a portal , bam 3 adds, so I start mezzing the adds, 3 can be difficult for bards since we don't have an AE mez, but i am getting the job done.  Then I start noticing a message &quot;SoandSo's Corpse awakens a vann miltilis&quot;  So I remez, about the 3rd time I noticed the corpse part and ask if a DoT went off, and all he says is I didn't know what to do.  How could a 66 shammy not know what to do in a situation like that??? You target your tank and type /assist.  Well, all in all what makes me mad is that we would have been able to handle it if he hadn't dotted that mob.   Tank almost had the first mob down when he died and cleric had a mob pounding on her the whole time due to the DoT on the mob.  Oh well good thing we had a wizzy to EVAC!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
<br />

<br />
I just love being a bard!!!!!!</span></td>
