			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Crowd Control<a name="71870"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 5 05 3:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It's a fact that a LOT of tanks (especially pallies using stun aggro, or warriors addicted to bows) use the puller as an assist. They assist whoever is pulling to get a mob on target quickly and start casting stuns or shooting arrows to generate aggro and get it as fast as they can. 
<br />

<br />
As a bar you should KNOW this, and be sure to look in your group. If you are the only means of C.C. in the group, as well as the puller (which happens more often than not) you haev a couple choises: 
<br />

<br />
1) Live with it. Knowing that the tank is going to assist you for target and most likely break the mob you just mezzed occcationally you should be mezzing the mobs further away out of line of site and when you come into the camp have the mob you want them to kill on target. OR - just accecpt the fact that when multiple mobs you will have to &quot;re-mezz&quot; at least one. The BIG key to this style is to make sure and tell the rest of the group to ASSIST THE TANK and not you; and to tell the tank that he should NEVER switch targets unless YOU call it. Some tanks have a tendency to break a mezz, see the broken mezz message, and then switch targets because tehy think they are on the wrong mob (which results in them breaking another mezz) -- Yes, those tanks are fools, but they do exist. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
2) Tell the group to assist the TANK and not you, and tell the tank not to assist you for target. Simply ask the tank to ALWAYS target the SECOND mob that comes into the camp on any multi pull. You can explain why if you need to, but hopefull that will not be necessary. If the tank grabs the second mob that leaves you free to mezz the first, and still have time to swap targets and slow the second one, before you need to start spining HoS/ Mezz on the first, third and fourth.. This usually works like a charm once your tank gets used to letting you deal with the first mob.
<br />

<br />
The tough part is getting your tank to undertand that while you MAY be the puller, you are MORE IMPORTANTLY the C.C. You are NOT a monk, and no matter how many monks tell him different a BARD's pulling style is completely different. -- 
<br />

<br />
On the other hand, if you are a bard, and you pull like a monk instead of using your tools (mezz, snare, highsun, slow, lull,  charm- and occationally fade) then it's your fault the group gets killed. Not the fault of those that break your 1 mezz. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
