<br />

<br />
Hmm.. who said anything about pulling singles? Pulling singles is usually over protecting your group, and at the very least boring  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
I was talking about puling styles.. not puling singles... Monks tag (lull at times) and basically run back to the raid and flop. Sometimes they use building, stairs, corners and flopping to seperate mob; sometimes not. Bard happen to use a completely different set of tools to accomplish these tasks. Also.. If the bard is the mezzer.... he's not a monk that is just gonna flop and go pull again. He/she is a class that will have to do C.C. .. ie mezzing/slowing etc.. and therefore assisting them while they are pulling is a bit on the retarded side.
<br />

<br />
Qvic raids on the Msha's most cetainly CAN be done pulling singles.. although Why you'd want to is beyond me. It's too slow, and its boring as H. E. Double hockey sticks. BUT-- a bard puller certainly CAN mezz mobs while pulling multiples into the camp. I do it all the time. .. You grab a bunch of mobs and use mezz on the way back to the camp to seperate them by a couple seconds. The caster mobs stop to cast, or create pets and you run around a bit and mezz those pets (the Msha's specifically). By the time your mezz wears off the pets are gone. All those things seperate incomming mobs by a second or 2.. even when it's NOT a single pull. That second or 2 is enough for bards/chanters to do any CC work that needs to be done (unless you have the tanks/healers to just off tank everything) 
<br />

<br />
-- Pulling single was not the point of my post, or the thread for that matter.. it was a rant about people breaking mezz, and I was simply pointing out that a little planning ahead with your tank can go a long way tword solving that... On a raid and in a group. ...
<br />

<br />
But just for fun one day .. do this.. When you pull a Msha from deep in the building.. use Bard DA to get to it.. drag everything in the building out into the open area in front of the building.. Run it all in a circle backtracking it away from the raid. Since the Msha is at the end of your line of mobs (it runs slower and will stop to cast at least once) .. Hit fade and double back around. Re-tag the Msha (or have someone else tag it) -- then use nearest target hotkeys to target and mezz its pets on the way back to the camp. .. BINGO - Single pulled Msha with a bare min. of clearing in front of the building before you go get it. -- It's a lot of fun, and it really isn't hard.</span></td>
